HEADWORD: Lions tail
<hw>Li"on's tail`</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"⟦ucr⟧nz t⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of labiate plants
(<gen>Leonurus</gen>); -- so called from a fancied resemblance of its
flower spikes to the tuft of a lion's tail. <spn>Leonurus Cardiaca</spn>
is the common <stype>motherwort</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lion's tooth</ent>⟦br⟧
